1118578404243247104.text: We make steps every day towards returning astronauts to space from US soil! The CFT engine and booster are in final production in Decatur and will be headed to Cape Canaveral soon! 1119754804258062337.text: NASA has been notified about the results of the @SpaceX Static Fire Test and the anomaly that occurred during the final test. We will work closely to ensure we safely move forward with our Commercial Crew Program.pic.twitter.com/yE2J5yGzA7

1116404828656291840.text: These four @NASA_Astronauts are training to fly on @SpaceX's #CrewDragon spacecraft- as the crew and backup crew. How have our astronauts been preparing for flight on @BoeingSpace and SpaceX's spacecraft ? https://go.nasa.gov/2P8JDk0 pic.twitter.com/tzuIlf7kTk

1117794256373067776.text:
Astronauts @AstroIronMike, @AstroDuke and Barry “Butch” Wilmore spent some time training in the Free Flyer Track & Capture Sim in @nasajohnson's Cupola mock-up .

This training is an important part of learning how to work on the @Space_Station: https://go.nasa.gov/2IgpoAg pic.twitter.com/WC2VBSRczo

1104027761205788672.text: After the @SpaceX fast recovery boats have safed the #CrewDragon, the recovery teams will prepare to lift it atop the Go Searcher recovery ship and place it in the cradle.pic.twitter.com/Ah8txjGnDF

1116840550299262978.text: Astronauts have been hard at work training in the Neutral Buoyancy Lab at @NASA_Johnson . Learn more about what it takes to fly aboard @BoeingSpace and @SpaceX spacecraft: https://go.nasa.gov/2IgpoAg pic.twitter.com/dViQpeVpaJ

1104025964596604928.text:
We were lucky to check out the interfaces during #CrewDragon's Demo-1 mission. Everything worked perfectly. Later this year, we are going to install a second docking adapter to support an additional spacecraft docking simultaneously to station. 
~Kenny Todd. @Space_Stationpic.twitter.com/7ExtKPcAtO

1104031899889135620.text: The @SpaceX recovery team have lowered the hydraulic lift on Go Searcher. After the #CrewDragon is aboard the ship, it will be moved into a hangar on the ship and secured for the roughly 30 hour trip back to Cape Canaveral.pic.twitter.com/OwB2Cw4EIp

.@NASA and the @DeptofDefense Human Space Flight Support Office Rescue Division are conducting search and rescue training exercises at the Army Warf on Cape Canaveral Air Force Station and in the Atlantic Ocean :

1113118867025551361.text:
.@BoeingSpace and @SpaceX are getting ready to launch astronauts from U.S. soil, but getting off the ground is just the beginning. 

Once they arrive at the @Space_Station, astronauts will be working on research to improve life on Earth : https://go.nasa.gov/1EIx5m6 pic.twitter.com/Py0cLYgS88

1104033728593121281.text: The #CrewDragon completed its Demo-1 flight test this morning. The spacecraft successfully splashed down in the Atlantic Ocean at 8:45 a.m. ET. It has been lifted out of the ocean and is now securely seated in @SpaceX's cradle aboard the Go Searcher Recovery ship.pic.twitter.com/w8nuZZBd1Q
